# cf-cache-audit

> **Analyse a website's assets and determine which are served from Cloudflare cache and which are not.**

`cf-cache-audit` is a production-quality terminal tool that crawls any website, discovers all static assets (images, CSS, JS, fonts, videos, SVGs, manifests…), and validates their Cloudflare cache status. It produces a rich, colour-coded terminal report plus optional JSON and CSV exports.

---

## Features

| Category | Details |
|---|---|
| **Crawling** | Recursive page crawl with configurable depth, `robots.txt`, `sitemap.xml` |
| **Asset Discovery** | Parses `<img>`, `<script>`, `<link>`, `<video>`, `<audio>`, `<source>`, `<iframe>`, inline `style`, `<style>` blocks, CSS `url()` and `@font-face`, JS dynamic imports |
| **Framework Detection** | Next.js, React, Angular, Vue, WordPress, Drupal, static |
| **Cloudflare Detection** | `server: cloudflare`, `cf-ray`, `cf-cache-status`, APO, Cache Rules hints |
| **CDN Detection** | Cloudflare, Akamai, CloudFront, Fastly, Google, Azure, Bunny, StackPath, KeyCDN, Sucuri |
| **Cache Validation** | HEAD → GET fallback, retry with exponential back-off, rate limiting |
| **Warm-Cache Testing** | Multi-probe MISS → HIT transition detection |
| **Reporting** | Rich terminal table, summary panel, JSON export, CSV export |
| **Performance** | asyncio + aiohttp, configurable concurrency, token-bucket rate limiter |

---

## Installation

### Prerequisites

- **Python 3.12+**

### From source

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/cf-cache-audit.git
cd cf-cache-audit

# Create virtual environment
python3.12 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

# Install in editable mode
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

### Quick install (dependencies only)

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Usage

### Basic scan

```bash
cf-cache-audit https://example.com
```

### With options

```bash
cf-cache-audit https://example.com \
    --depth 2 \
    --workers 30 \
    --timeout 20 \
    --json report.json \
    --csv report.csv \
    --verbose
```

### Warm-cache testing

```bash
cf-cache-audit https://example.com --warm-cache --warm-cache-attempts 5
```

### Follow subdomains

```bash
cf-cache-audit https://example.com --follow-subdomains --depth 1
```

### As a Python module

```bash
python -m cf_cache_audit https://example.com
```

---

## CLI Options

| Option | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `url` | *(required)* | Domain name or URL to audit |
| `--depth N` | `3` | Maximum crawl depth for internal pages |
| `--timeout N` | `15` | HTTP request timeout in seconds |
| `--workers N` | `20` | Number of concurrent workers |
| `--json FILE` | — | Export full report to JSON |
| `--csv FILE` | — | Export asset data to CSV |
| `--follow-subdomains` | `false` | Also crawl pages on subdomains |
| `--warm-cache` | `false` | Test cache warm-up (multiple requests per asset) |
| `--warm-cache-attempts N` | `3` | Number of probes per asset in warm-cache mode |
| `--verbose, -v` | `false` | Show detailed messages and debug logging |
| `--version, -V` | — | Show version and exit |

